`docs/` is the project's design memory for the CTX system: it's where an
editor learns *why* the current architecture looks the way it does before
touching any crate, script, or template. Nothing here is executable —
depending on this directory means reading it, not linking against it.

The six files form a strict hierarchy that editors must respect. `SPEC.md`
is the frozen, sealed contract (rev 4) — current behavior, thresholds, and
file-format rules; changes require explicit re-spec, not ad hoc edits.
`DECISIONS.md` is the append-only rationale log (ADR-001..046) explaining
why SPEC looks the way it does and which alternatives were tried and
rejected — check it before reintroducing anything that smells like a
prior design (git-diff freshness, `/dev/null` masks, fixed cage aliases,
API-key egress). `STATUS.md` is the only doc expected to go stale on
purpose; it tracks current state and next steps against ADR numbers and
must never absorb design decisions that belong in SPEC or DECISIONS.
`UNIMPLEMENTED.md` is the backlog/changelog hybrid — its step numbering
*is* the project history, so new work appends rather than renumbers, and
several DONE markers there correspond to real crates that must be checked
before being reverted to "pending." `SANDBOX.md` and `DYLINT_RULES.md` are
narrower: the former is explicitly retired (superseded by the hook-led
`ctx-context`/`ctx-cage` model in SPEC/DECISIONS) and kept only as
historical threat-model record; the latter specifies nine dylint rules,
none implemented, two of which (rules 1 and 4) have mechanical stand-ins
in `scripts/` (`rationale_check.py`, `cycle_check.sh`) that must stay in
sync until the real lints exist.

The shared invariant across all six: none restate architecture that
SPEC.md or DECISIONS.md already own — STATUS, UNIMPLEMENTED, SANDBOX, and
DYLINT_RULES all point back rather than duplicate. Any edit that changes
the rollup/leaf `.ctx` line budgets must touch both SPEC.md and
`prompts/summarizer-rollup.md` together, since the numbers are asserted
identical.

No `intent.md` exists for this directory, so no divergence check applies.